OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F415A1779210357
OL,3,CMeningitis outbreak: Which schools and
OL,4,Ccolleges are affected?
OL,6,FWhat is the advice for young people
OL,7,Fand parents at schools with confirmed
OL,8,Fmeningitis cases?
OL,10,FThe UKHSA says the risk to the wider
OL,11,Fpublic 'remains low', but students and
OL,12,Fparents at affected schools are being
OL,13,Freminded of the symptoms of meningitis.
OL,15,FClose contacts of pupils who have
OL,16,Fmeningitis have already been offered
OL,17,Fantibiotics, which the UKHSA says is a
OL,18,Fprecautionary measure.
OL,20,FStudents should continue to attend
OL,21,Fschool as usual.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/8
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
